-- Monex Group Drops in Tokyo on Share Sale, Citigroup Plan to Reduce Stake
-- B y   K y u n g   B o k   C h o
-- 2010-09-22T00:19:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-22/monex-group-drops-in-tokyo-on-share-sale-citigroup-plan-to-reduce-stake.html
Monex Group Inc. fell the most in
six months in Tokyo trading after saying it will sell shares in
Japan and that Citigroup Inc. will cut its stake to 3.6 percent
from 20.6 percent.  The Japanese provider of investment services dropped 7
percent to 28,500 yen as of 9:17 a.m. on the Tokyo Stock
Exchange, headed for the biggest decline since March 19. The
benchmark Topix index slid 0.4 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kyung Bok Cho at 
 kcho7@bloomberg.net  